          <p class="style8">RSPB Scotland Loch of Kinnordy</p>
          <p align="center" class="style2">
            We are very fortunate to have on our village doorstep, the
            <strong>RSPB Loch of Kinnordy Reserve</strong>. This shallow loch is
            situated in a natural basin surrounded by farmland and attracts all
            types of <strong>wildlife</strong>. One favourite summer visitor is
            the <strong>osprey</strong> which you can see fishing around the
            loch, while in the winter <strong>whooper swans</strong> and
            <strong>geese</strong> fly in. There are three purpose built hides
            and you're just as likely to see<strong> otters</strong>,
            <strong>red squirrels</strong> and <strong>deer</strong> as
            <strong>wildfowl</strong> not to mention many species of<strong>
              butterflies</strong
            >
            and <strong>dragonflies</strong>. The reserve is open daily from
            dawn to dusk and entrance is free of charge with a voluntary
            donation cairn at the entrance.
          </p>
