    <tr>
      <td width="741">
        <div align="left">
          <p class="style7">Is Loch of Kinnordy Natural or Man-made?</p>
          <p class="style2">
            Probably both. Historic maps show that there has always been a wet,
            boggy area in this location, although there is evidence that it was
            used for growing crops in the very distant past. In the early
            1800&rsquo;s it became an industrial site, as the Gairey Burn, which
            takes water away from the loch and down to Kirriemuir, was blasted
            to lower the bed level, and therefore lower the loch. This, together
            with an embankment, allowed the level of the loch to be lowered, and
            Marl was then extracted and taken away for use on surrounding
            farmland. When this work ceased the land was left to re-flood and
            the beginnings of what you see now were formed.
          </p>
        </div>
